can i get pregnant if i have sex while my period is on if i am taking birth control pills if you are taking your pills properly and the pills are working properly within your body no because you have not ovulated the period you get when you are on the pill is not a true period it is called withdrawl bleeding the progesterone in the pill tricks your body into thinking it is pregnant thereby shutting down the ovaries preventing ovulation and building up the uterine lining during the week of non active pills the drop in the level of progesterone makes your body think you have had a miscarriage and so it sheds the uterine lining you are still fully protected during the week of non active pills Menstrual cycle Oral contraceptive Progesterone Polycystic ovary syndrome Fertility awareness Birth control Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Endometriosis Estrus cycle Pregnancy Ovary Obstetrics Puberty Ovulation Miscarriage Gynaecology Ectopic pregnancy Depo Provera Ovarian cancer Ovarian cyst Human chorionic gonadotropin Gynecologic hemorrhage Intrauterine device Acne Endometrial cancer Abortion debate Tocopherol Abortion EastEnders Uterine fibroids Dysfunctional uterine bleeding Premature birth Hormone replacement therapy Lipoid congenital adrenal hyperplasia Baldness treatments In vitro fertilisation Vaginal bleeding Uterus Sexual abstinence Breastfeeding Twin Endometrium Pregnancy test Neighbours Psoriasis Morning sickness Sexual reproduction Gregory Goodwin Pincus Sex education Fertilisation Niddah Urinary incontinence Religion and abortion Infertility Pelvic inflammatory disease Androgen insensitivity syndrome Testosterone Caffeine Congenital adrenal hyperplasia due to 17 alpha-hydroxylase deficiency Progesterone only pill Spina bifida Chemical abortion Swyer syndrome Partial-birth abortion Resident Evil Outbreak: File 2 The Inside Folic acid Luteinizing hormone Habitual abortion Anovulation Oxytocin Resident Evil Outbreak Carpel Flowering plant Vitamin D Homosexuality a